 In <span class=\\\"html-italic\\\">Proceedings of the 2020 Tenth International Conference on Image Processing Theory, Tools and Applications (IPTA)</span>; IEEE: New York, NY, USA, 2020; pp. 1–6. [<a href=\\\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=SegTHOR:+Segmentation+of+thoracic+organs+at+risk+in+CT+images&amp;author=Lambert,+Z.&amp;author=Petitjean,+C.&amp;author=Dubray,+B.&amp;author=Kuan,+S.&amp;publication_year=2020&amp;pages=1%E2%80%936\\\" class=\\\"google-scholar\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\">Google Scholar</a>]</li><li id=\\\"B44-applsci-16-04199\\\" class=\\\"html-xx\\\" data-content=\\\"44.\\\">Ji, Y.; Bai, H.; Ge, C.; Yang, J.; Zhu, Y.; Zhang, R.; Li, Z.; Zhanng, L.; Ma, W.; Wan, X.; et al. AMOS: A large-scale abdominal multi-organ benchmark for versatile medical image segmentation. In <span class=\\\"html-italic\\\">Advances in Neural Information Processing Systems (NeurIPS)</span>; IEEE: New York, NY, USA, 2022; Volume 35, pp. 36722–36732. [<a href=\\\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=AMOS:+A+large-scale+abdominal+multi-organ+benchmark+for+versatile+medical+image+segmentation&amp;author=Ji,+Y.&amp;author=Bai,+H.&amp;author=Ge,+C.&amp;author=Yang,+J.&amp;author=Zhu,+Y.&amp;author=Zhang,+R.&amp;author=Li,+Z.&amp;author=Zhanng,+L.&amp;author=Ma,+W.&amp;author=Wan,+X.&amp;author=et+al.&amp;publication_year=2022&amp;pages=36722%E2%80%9336732\\\" class=\\\"google-scholar\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\">Google Scholar</a>]</li><li id=\\\"B45-applsci-16-04199\\\" class=\\\"html-xx\\\" data-content=\\\"45.\\\">Bernard, O.; Lalande, A.; Zotti, C.; Cervenansky, F.; Yang, X.; Heng, P.A.; Cetin, I.; Lekadir, K.; Camara, O.; Ballester, M.A.G.; et al. Deep learning techniques for automatic MRI cardiac multi-structures segmentation and diagnosis: Is the problem solved? <span class=\\\"html-italic\\\">IEEE Trans. Med. Imaging</span> <b>2018</b>, <span class=\\\"html-italic\\\">37</span>, 2514–2525. [<a href=\\\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Deep+learning+techniques+for+automatic+MRI+cardiac+multi-structures+segmentation+and+diagnosis:+Is+the+problem+solved?&amp;author=Bernard,+O.&amp;author=Lalande,+A.&amp;author=Zotti,+C.&amp;author=Cervenansky,+F.&amp;author=Yang,+X.&amp;author=Heng,+P.A.&amp;author=Cetin,+I.&amp;author=Lekadir,+K.&amp;author=Camara,+O.&amp;author=Ballester,+M.A.G.&amp;author=et+al.&amp;publication_year=2018&amp;journal=IEEE+Trans.+Med.+Imaging&amp;volume=37&amp;pages=2514%E2%80%932525&amp;doi=10.1109/TMI.2018.2837502&amp;pmid=29994302\\\" class=\\\"google-scholar\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\\\"https://doi.org/10.1109/TMI.2018.2837502\\\" class=\\\"cross-ref\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\">CrossRef</a>] [<a href=\\\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/29994302\\\" class=\\\"cross-ref pub_med\\\" data-typ=\\\"pmid\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\">PubMed</a>]</li><li id=\\\"B46-applsci-16-04199\\\" class=\\\"html-xx\\\" data-content=\\\"46.\\\">Antonelli, M.; Reinke, A.; Bakas, S.; Farahani, K.; Kopp-Schneider, A.; Landman, B.A.; Litjens, G.; Menze, B.; Ronneberger, O.; Summers, R.M.; et al. The medical segmentation decathlon. <span class=\\\"html-italic\\\">Nat. Commun.</span> <b>2022</b>, <span class=\\\"html-italic\\\">13</span>, 4128. [<a href=\\\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=The+medical+segmentation+decathlon&amp;author=Antonelli,+M.&amp;author=Reinke,+A.&amp;author=Bakas,+S.&amp;author=Farahani,+K.&amp;author=Kopp-Schneider,+A.&amp;author=Landman,+B.A.&amp;author=Litjens,+G.&amp;author=Menze,+B.&amp;author=Ronneberger,+O.&amp;author=Summers,+R.M.&amp;author=et+al.&amp;publication_year=2022&amp;journal=Nat.+Commun.&amp;volume=13&amp;pages=4128&amp;doi=10.1038/s41467-022-30695-9\\\" class=\\\"google-scholar\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\\\"https://doi.org/10.1038/s41467-022-30695-9\\\" class=\\\"cross-ref\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\">CrossRef</a>]</li><li id=\\\"B47-applsci-16-04199\\\" class=\\\"html-xx\\\" data-content=\\\"47.\\\">Heller, N.; Isensee, F.; Tejpaul, R.; Wood, A.; Papanikolopoulos, N.; Weight, C. The 2023 Kidney and Kidney Tumor Segmentation Challenge (KiTS23). In <span class=\\\"html-italic\\\">Kidney and Kidney Tumor Segmentation: MICCAI 2023 Challenge, KiTS 2023</span>; Springer: Cham, Switzerland, 2024; pp. 1–10. [<a href=\\\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=The+2023+Kidney+and+Kidney+Tumor+Segmentation+Challenge+(KiTS23)&amp;author=Heller,+N.&amp;author=Isensee,+F.&amp;author=Tejpaul,+R.&amp;author=Wood,+A.&amp;author=Papanikolopoulos,+N.&amp;author=Weight,+C.&amp;publication_year=2024&amp;pages=1%E2%80%9310\\\" class=\\\"google-scholar\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\">Google Scholar</a>]</li></ol>\"},{\"depth\":1,\"heading\":\"FiguresandTables\",\"html\":\"<div class=\\\"html-fig_show  mfp-hide\\\" id=\\\"fig_body_display_applsci-16-04199-f001\\\">\\n  <div class=\\\"html-caption\\\"> <b>Figure 1.</b>\\n      Overall architecture of the proposed VMMedSAM-X framework. The framework consists of three main components: a multi-scale state-enhanced encoder, a prompt encoder, and a mask decoder. The input image is first processed by the proposed encoder, which integrates SS2D and xLSTM to capture long-range dependencies with linear computational complexity. The prompt encoder accepts user-provided prompts (e.g., boxes or points) to provide positional guidance. The mask decoder then fuses the encoded image features with the prompt information to generate the final segmentation mask.</div>\\n  <div class=\\\"html-img\\\"><a href=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g001.png\\\" class=\\\"html-img-zoom\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><img data-large=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g001.png\\\" data-original=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g001.png\\\" alt=\\\"Applsci 16 04199 g001\\\" title=\\\"Applsci 16 04199 g001\\\" data-lsrc=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g001.png\\\" src=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g001.png\\\"></a></div>\\n</div>\\n<div class=\\\"html-fig_show  mfp-hide\\\" id=\\\"fig_body_display_applsci-16-04199-f002\\\">\\n  <div class=\\\"html-caption\\\"> <b>Figure 2.</b>\\n      Architecture of the multi-scale state-enhanced encoder. The encoder adopts a four-stage pyramidal structure. Stage 1 and Stage 2 consist of SS2D blocks; Stage 3 and Stage 4 incorporate cross-attention fusion blocks with SS2D and xLSTM branches. The numbers of blocks in each stage are detailed in <a href=\\\"#sec3dot2-applsci-16-04199\\\" class=\\\"html-sec\\\">Section 3.2</a>.</div>\\n  <div class=\\\"html-img\\\"><a href=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g002.png\\\" class=\\\"html-img-zoom\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><img data-large=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g002.png\\\" data-original=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g002.png\\\" alt=\\\"Applsci 16 04199 g002\\\" title=\\\"Applsci 16 04199 g002\\\" data-lsrc=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g002.png\\\" src=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g002.png\\\"></a></div>\\n</div>\\n<div class=\\\"html-fig_show  mfp-hide\\\" id=\\\"fig_body_display_applsci-16-04199-f003\\\">\\n  <div class=\\\"html-caption\\\"> <b>Figure 3.</b>\\n      Illustration of the proposed dual-path cross-attention fusion module. The module consists of two parallel branches: an SS2D-based branch for spatial structural feature encoding and an xLSTM-based branch for semantic memory modeling. High-level features are first projected into sequence representations and processed by xLSTM to capture long-range semantic dependencies. Bidirectional cross-attention is then employed to enable information interaction between the structural and semantic feature streams, facilitating adaptive feature fusion and enhancing global context modeling capability.</div>\\n  <div class=\\\"html-img\\\"><a href=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g003.png\\\" class=\\\"html-img-zoom\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><img data-large=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g003.png\\\" data-original=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g003.png\\\" alt=\\\"Applsci 16 04199 g003\\\" title=\\\"Applsci 16 04199 g003\\\" data-lsrc=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g003.png\\\" src=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g003.png\\\"></a></div>\\n</div>\\n<div class=\\\"html-fig_show  mfp-hide\\\" id=\\\"fig_body_display_applsci-16-04199-f004\\\">\\n  <div class=\\\"html-caption\\\"> <b>Figure 4.</b>\\n      Qualitative segmentation results on the segTHOR dataset. From left to right: input image, ground truth, U-Net, TransUNet, SwinUNet, MedSAM, VM-UNet, and the proposed VMMedSAM-X.</div>\\n  <div class=\\\"html-img\\\"><a href=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g004.png\\\" class=\\\"html-img-zoom\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><img data-large=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g004.png\\\" data-original=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g004.png\\\" alt=\\\"Applsci 16 04199 g004\\\" title=\\\"Applsci 16 04199 g004\\\" data-lsrc=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g004.png\\\" src=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g004.png\\\"></a></div>\\n</div>\\n<div class=\\\"html-fig_show  mfp-hide\\\" id=\\\"fig_body_display_applsci-16-04199-f005\\\">\\n  <div class=\\\"html-caption\\\"> <b>Figure 5.</b>\\n      Qualitative segmentation results on the MSD-Lung dataset. From left to right: input image, ground truth, U-Net, TransUNet, SwinUNet, MedSAM, VM-UNet, and the proposed VMMedSAM-X.</div>\\n  <div class=\\\"html-img\\\"><a href=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g005.png\\\" class=\\\"html-img-zoom\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><img data-large=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g005.png\\\" data-original=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g005.png\\\" alt=\\\"Applsci 16 04199 g005\\\" title=\\\"Applsci 16 04199 g005\\\" data-lsrc=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g005.png\\\" src=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g005.png\\\"></a></div>\\n</div>\\n<div class=\\\"html-fig_show  mfp-hide\\\" id=\\\"fig_body_display_applsci-16-04199-f006\\\">\\n  <div class=\\\"html-caption\\\"> <b>Figure 6.</b>\\n      Qualitative segmentation results on the KiTS23 dataset. From left to right: input image, ground truth, U-Net, TransUNet, SwinUNet, MedSAM, VM-UNet, and the proposed VMMedSAM-X.</div>\\n  <div class=\\\"html-img\\\"><a href=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g006.png\\\" class=\\\"html-img-zoom\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><img data-large=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g006.png\\\" data-original=\\\"/applsci/applsci-16-04199/article_deploy/html/images/applsci-16-04199-g006.png\\\" alt=\\\"Applsci 16 04199 g00